## net device feature bit

| Feature Name                     | Bitmap Value | Description                                         |
|:-------------------------------- |:------------:|:--------------------------------------------------- |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_CSUM                | 0            | Host handles pkts w/ partial csum                   |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_GUEST_CSUM          | 1            | Guest handles pkts w/ partial csum                  |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_CTRL_GUEST_OFFLOADS | 2            | Dynamic offload configuration                       |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_MTU                 | 3            | Initial MTU advice                                  |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_MAC                 | 5            | Host has given MAC address                          |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_GSO                 | 6 (Legacy)   | Host handles pkts w/ any GSO type                   |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_GUEST_TSO4          | 7            | Guest can handle TSOv4 in                           |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_GUEST_TSO6          | 8            | Guest can handle TSOv6 in                           |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_GUEST_ECN           | 9            | Guest can handle TSO\[6] w/ ECN in                  |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_GUEST_UFO           | 10           | Guest can handle UFO in                             |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_HOST_TSO4           | 11           | Host can handle TSOv4 in                            |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_HOST_TSO6           | 12           | Host can handle TSOv6 in                            |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_HOST_ECN            | 13           | Host can handle TSO\[6] w/ ECN in                   |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_HOST_UFO            | 14           | Host can handle UFO in                              |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_MRG_RXBUF           | 15           | Host can merge receive buffers                      |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_STATUS              | 16           | virtio_net_config.status available                  |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_CTRL_VQ             | 17           | Control channel available                           |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_CTRL_RX             | 18           | Control channel RX mode support                     |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_CTRL_VLAN           | 19           | Control channel VLAN filtering                      |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_CTRL_RX_EXTRA       | 20           | Extra RX mode control support                       |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_GUEST_ANNOUNCE      | 21           | Guest can announce device on the network            |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_MQ                  | 22           | Device supports Receive Flow Steering               |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_CTRL_MAC_ADDR       | 23           | Set MAC address                                     |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_HASH_REPORT         | 57           | Supports hash report                                |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_RSS                 | 60           | Supports RSS RX steering                            |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_RSC_EXT             | 61           | Extended coalescing info                            |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_STANDBY             | 62           | Act as standby for another device with the same MAC |
| VIRTIO_NET_F_SPEED_DUPLEX        | 63           | Device set linkspeed and duplex                     |

## virtio feature bit

| Feature Name               | Bitmap Value | Description                                                                   |
|:-------------------------- |:------------:|:----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| VIRTIO_TRANSPORT_F_START   | 28           | 用于传输的起始特性位（如 virtio_ring, virtio_pci 等）                                       |
| VIRTIO_TRANSPORT_F_END     | 41           | 用于传输的结束特性位                                                                    |
| VIRTIO_F_NOTIFY_ON_EMPTY   | 24           | 是否在 ring 完全使用时获得回调，即使我们已经抑制了它们？                                               |
| VIRTIO_F_ANY_LAYOUT        | 27           | 设备是否可以处理任何描述符布局？                                                              |
| VIRTIO_F_VERSION_1         | 32           | 符合 v1.0 的特性位                                                                  |
| VIRTIO_F_ACCESS_PLATFORM   | 33           | 如果清除-设备具有平台 DMA（例如 IOMMU）绕过 quirk 特性。如果设置-使用平台 DMA 工具访问内存。 注意与大多数其他特性相比的反向极性。 |
| VIRTIO_F_RING_PACKED       | 34           | 此特性表示对打包的 virtqueue 布局的支持。                                                    |
| VIRTIO_F_IN_ORDER          | 35           | Inorder 特性表示设备按照它们被提供的顺序使用所有缓冲区。                                              |
| VIRTIO_F_ORDER_PLATFORM    | 36           | 此特性表示驱动程序和设备按照平台描述的方式对内存访问进行排序。                                               |
| VIRTIO_F_SR_IOV            | 37           | 设备是否支持 Single Root I/O Virtualization?                                        |
| VIRTIO_F_NOTIFICATION_DATA | 38           | 此特性表示驱动程序在其设备通知中传递额外的数据（除了标识 virtqueue）。                                      |
| VIRTIO_F_RING_RESET        | 40           | 此特性表示驱动程序可以单独重置队列。                                                            |

## vring flag bit

| Macro Name                      | Value | Description                                                                                           |
|:------------------------------- |:----- |:----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| VRING_DESC_F_NEXT               | 1     | This marks a buffer as continuing via the next field.                                                 |
| VRING_DESC_F_WRITE              | 2     | This marks a buffer as write-only (otherwise read-only).                                              |
| VRING_DESC_F_INDIRECT           | 4     | This means the buffer contains a list of buffer descriptors.                                          |
| VRING_PACKED_DESC_F_AVAIL       | 7     | Mark a descriptor as available in packed ring (defined as shifts).                                    |
| VRING_PACKED_DESC_F_USED        | 15    | Mark a descriptor as used in packed ring (defined as shifts).                                         |
| VRING_USED_F_NO_NOTIFY          | 1     | Host's advice to Guest: don't kick when adding a buffer (unreliable optimization).                    |
| VRING_AVAIL_F_NO_INTERRUPT      | 1     | Guest's advice to Host: don't interrupt when consuming a buffer (unreliable optimization).            |
| VRING_PACKED_EVENT_FLAG_ENABLE  | 0x0   | Enable events in packed ring.                                                                         |
| VRING_PACKED_EVENT_FLAG_DISABLE | 0x1   | Disable events in packed ring.                                                                        |
| VRING_PACKED_EVENT_FLAG_DESC    | 0x2   | Enable events for a specific descriptor in packed ring (valid if VIRTIO_RING_F_EVENT_IDX negotiated). |
| VRING_PACKED_EVENT_F_WRAP_CTR   | 15    | Wrap counter bit shift in event suppression structure of packed ring.                                 |
| VIRTIO_RING_F_INDIRECT_DESC     | 28    | Support for indirect buffer descriptors.                                                              |
| VIRTIO_RING_F_EVENT_IDX         | 29    | Host/Guest publishes index for expected interrupt/kick (ignore the flags field of avail/used ring).   |
